 P( A \cap B)=P(A \mid B) \cdot P(B) \Leftrightarrow P(A \mid B)=\frac{P( A \cap B)}{P(B)}  
P(A \mid B) 
P(A \mid B)= \frac {something}{P(B)} 
P(B \mid A)P(A)
P(B \cap A)
P(A \cap B)=P(B \cap A)
P(A \mid B)=\frac{P(B\cap A)}{P(B)}
P(B \cap A)=P(B\mid A) \cdot P(A)
P(B\mid A)
P(A \mid B)=\frac{P(B \mid A) \cdot P(A)}{P(B)}
P(A\mid B) = \dfrac{P(B\mid A)\times P(A)}{P(B)}
P(A \cap B) = P(A \mid B)\times P(B)
